      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEY LACEY (8) was in the minors two back (23.08) at this track but ran below best last time there, finishing 8th. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. ORANA WILLOW (2) hit the ground running and never headed to claim a maiden victory two back then finished a 6 length third last start at this track over 400m (23.35). Returns to the scene of her maiden win. Bold showing expected again. BUNRATTY MAC (1) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at Gunnedah, but prior to that won by 0.8 lengths at Temora (19.08) beating Even If in a Grade 5 on June 24. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. EAR MUFFS (3) was unplaced here last start but gets his chance to atone.",
